        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-12 17:13:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJess - This submission is to cherrypick recent commits from master into el-alto branch. I included original release files also to this branch for consistency and release verify job failed (as expected). Is it okay to override this and do the merge? Going forward the new release candidate yamls will be created only on this branch (until el-alto is signed off)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "c1cdc99cc035f78f588d4866eb4ac4ca4cac642a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-12 17:30:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThe process does not support multiple releases files in one shot. \nPlease add one at a time.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "a4e5d1d0313ce506a05bcd02cf36b8d6bee1132e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 93,
          "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
          "username": "vv770d"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-12 17:32:57.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nJess - Both 1.3.1 and 1.3.2 were already released from master branch; this change was to bring those files into El-Alto branch for consistency (and not intended to release these version). In this case, is it okay to override this verify failure?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "1bbee9313d64787914bf8e9819b3c94ae3093e9d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-12 17:58:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nNo, overriding verify will bring further problems since the release will attempt to re-release it and report another failure. \nBest way is not to cherry-pick these releases files from master. \nThe process is design so that if a release is coming from master, then the releases file will be placed on master. If a release is happening from el-alto, the releases will happen from el-alto branch\nbut the process will not support duplicate releases files in multiple branches",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "244c215649a8d4fc1193bcfd504e9133792fb80a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 93,
          "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
          "username": "vv770d"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-12 18:01:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nokay, thanks for clarifying. I can remove releases files from this cherrypick.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
